body:
* Tested with Android 9 and 10
* Passwords should be invisible to the accessibility services (@mohammadnaseri)

Finally after a long time a new version with some translation updates and some minor code changes. The hint to ask keyboards to disable any learning / personalization should help the privacy aware, thanks to @pedronveloso for this.

Now requires Android 4 or higher, but according to the Google Play statistics there are no users on older versions anyway.

* Tested with Android 8.1
* Norwegian Bokmål translation (by Allan Nordhøy)
* Italian translation
* Use new clipboard API for Android API level >= 11
* Disable personalized keyboard learning on password input, if supported (Pedro Veloso)
* Migrated build to Android Studio

- Greek translation (by Wasilis Mandratzis-Walz)
- Ukrainian translation (by sorenabell)
- Tested with Android 5.1
- Fixed gradient in new app icon

- Japanese translation (by Naofumi)
- Updated Spanish translation
- Tested with Android 5.0
- Use Material theme on Android 5.0
- Improved app icon

- Setup Transifex synchronisation
- Added Romanian translation (by ArianServ)
- Added Turkish translation (by Muhammed İyi)
- Updated French and Vietnamese translations
- Partial Arabic translation
- Support for right-to-left scripts

- Added Croatian translation (by Marijan Smetko, Novska, Croatia)
- Fixed another possible exception when launched from another app
- Tested with Android 4.4
Final fix for the possible crash on startup
- Fixed possible crash on start (especially when launched via Appsi)

- Fixed occasional crash on some Android 4.3 devices
- Dutch translation

- Keyboard should use no auto correction in URL input
- Bugfix: Removed screenshot blocking in Android prior to 3.0. This security fix caused a distorted screen on some Samsung devices running Android 2.2 or 2.3.
- Updated Czech translation
- Tested with Android 4.3
- Initial release 1.0

- Use density independent pixels
- Set copy button inactive when unusable
- Limit window width on large screens

- Remove NULL bytes from end of hashed passwords (fixes issue #1)
- Move all dimensions to resource file
- Added Spanish and Catalan translations.
- Added Russian and Polish translations.

- Remember last used site URL.
- Added Chinese (China, simplified) translation.

- Auto completion for recently used domain names
- Use Holo theme on Android 3.0 and newer
- Added xhdpi icon
- Enabled app on SD
- Tested with Android 4.1 Jelly Bean
- Security fix: Don't allow screenshots in recent apps menu

- Trim the URL to the domain part when "share" feature is used.
- Use monospaced font for displaying the hashed password.

- Korean translation (by Jongha Kim)
- Czech translation (by Ondřej Vodáček)

- Brazilian Portuguese translation (by Evandro)
- Updated Korean translation (by Jongha Kim)

- French translation
- Vietnamese translation (by Phan Anh)
